63
00:02:28,790 --> 00:02:32,590
And really it creates this circle of life
thing.

64
00:02:32,590 --> 00:02:34,459
China makes a lot of cheap goods.

65
00:02:34,459 --> 00:02:37,000
They’re packed into cardboard boxes,

66
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,680
and sent to the United States,

67
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:40,280
where they’re briefly,

68
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,750
and then thrown away.

69
00:02:41,750 --> 00:02:44,110
And all that waste ultimately makes a trip

70
00:02:44,110 --> 00:02:46,290
back to where it started—

71
00:02:46,290 --> 00:02:48,830
China—to be recycled.

72
00:02:48,830 --> 00:02:51,010
It’s beautiful.

73
00:02:51,010 --> 00:02:53,170
But the benefits of recycling the world’s
garbage

74
00:02:53,170 --> 00:02:55,069
went way beyond money.

75
00:02:55,069 --> 00:02:57,989
30 years of China's manufacturing boom

76
00:02:57,989 --> 00:03:00,130
was fueled by garbage,

77
00:03:00,130 --> 00:03:02,989
garbage the Chinese regime encouraged the
world

78
00:03:02,989 --> 00:03:04,829
to give to China.

79
00:03:04,829 --> 00:03:06,180
Take copper for instance.

80
00:03:06,180 --> 00:03:08,859
It’s essential to modern living.

81
00:03:08,859 --> 00:03:12,090
You can’t transmit power or information
without it.

82
00:03:12,090 --> 00:03:14,549
But why mine your own copper

83
00:03:14,549 --> 00:03:18,470
when the rest of the world is throwing theirs
away?

84
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:20,469
According to the book, Junkyard Planet,

85
00:03:20,469 --> 00:03:21,730
in 2012,

86
00:03:21,730 --> 00:03:23,549
almost half of China’s copper

87
00:03:23,549 --> 00:03:25,920
was made from recycled scrap.

88
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:27,939
And 70% of that scrap

89
00:03:27,939 --> 00:03:30,230
came from the United States.

90
00:03:30,230 --> 00:03:31,870
Same goes for plastic and paper.

91
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:33,519
It’s cheaper, quicker,

92
00:03:33,519 --> 00:03:36,299
and easier to recycle plastic and paper

93
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:40,219
than it is to drill oil wells or cut down
trees.

94
00:03:40,219 --> 00:03:43,930
And it’s a huge energy save on top of that.

95
00:03:43,930 --> 00:03:45,060
According to Bloomberg,

96
00:03:45,060 --> 00:03:47,790
“Recycling 1 ton of paper saves enough energy

97
00:03:47,790 --> 00:03:49,819
